# Privacy Policy

Effective date: May 6, 2026  
Last updated: May 6, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how Umar Afzal Khan ("we", "us", "our") handles your information when you use miniNotes (the "App").

## 1. Information We Collect

We collect only the data needed to run miniNotes:

1. Account data
- Email address
- Account ID from Firebase Authentication
- Sign-in method (email/password or Google Sign-In)

2. App content
- Notes you create and save
- Optional profile data such as display name and profile photo

3. App security data
- App lock settings (PIN or biometric/device lock preference)

4. Technical data
- Basic device/app information from the operating system and SDKs
- Notification token data (if notifications are enabled)

5. Ads-related data
- Data used by ad providers (such as AdMob) to show and measure ads, based on platform settings and permissions

## 2. How We Use Information

We use this information to:
- Let you sign in and use your account
- Save and sync your notes
- Provide security features like PIN or biometric lock
- Send account-related messages like email verification or password reset
- Show ads (where applicable)
- Keep the app secure and working correctly

## 3. Legal Bases for Processing (GDPR/UK GDPR)

If GDPR/UK GDPR applies, we process data under one or more of these legal bases:
- Contract (to provide the app features you request)
- Legitimate interests (to secure and improve the app)
- Consent (where required)
- Legal obligations

## 4. Third-Party Services

miniNotes uses trusted third-party services, including:
- Firebase Authentication
- Cloud Firestore
- Google Sign-In
- Firebase Cloud Messaging
- Google Mobile Ads (AdMob)

These services have their own privacy policies.

## 5. Where Data Is Stored

Your data may be stored:
- In cloud services (for account and sync features)
- On your device (for local/offline app features)

We keep data only for as long as needed to provide the app or meet legal requirements.

## 6. Account and Data Deletion

You can delete your account inside the app from Settings.

When deletion is completed, we remove account-related data such as:
- Authentication account data
- Cloud notes and profile records
- Related local app preferences on that device

If you need help, contact iumarafzalkhan@gmail.com.

## 7. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal data.

We may share data only with service providers needed to run the app, or when required by law.

## 8. International Data Transfers

Your data may be processed in countries outside your own as part of cloud services. We use reasonable safeguards where required.

## 9. Security

We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data.

## 10. Children's Privacy

miniNotes is for general audiences. If local law requires parental or guardian involvement for younger users, that requirement applies.

## 11. Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing of your data.

For requests, contact iumarafzalkhan@gmail.com.

